204
00:08:50.050 --> 00:08:53.010
What is this green powder?

205
00:08:53.010 --> 00:08:54.100
What is it?

206
00:08:54.100 --> 00:08:58.350
H-How should we know?!
We're only following your king's orders!

207
00:08:58.350 --> 00:08:58.980
Right?

208
00:08:58.980 --> 00:09:00.350
We're just deliverymen!

209
00:09:00.350 --> 00:09:01.060
– Run!
– Run!

210
00:09:04.860 --> 00:09:07.440
This dust... It can't be!

211
00:09:07.940 --> 00:09:10.030
Dance powder?!

212
00:09:10.530 --> 00:09:12.360
You've heard of it?

213
00:09:12.360 --> 00:09:16.200
Yes. It's more aptly known
as "rain-summoning powder".

214
00:09:16.200 --> 00:09:17.750
Rain-summoning?

215
00:09:17.750 --> 00:09:19.710
I heard about it secondhand,

216
00:09:19.710 --> 00:09:24.670
but it was supposedly created
by a scientist in a land with no rain.

217
00:09:24.670 --> 00:09:29.300
Combining it with rising smoke
creates a spreading mist in the sky,

218
00:09:29.300 --> 00:09:32.380
which artificially causes rainfall.

219
00:09:32.380 --> 00:09:34.350
And that's dance powder.

220
00:09:34.350 --> 00:09:38.100
The country who created
the powder almost danced for joy,

221
00:09:38.100 --> 00:09:40.810
and that's how it got its name.

222
00:09:41.310 --> 00:09:44.810
However, for every action
there's a reaction.

223
00:09:44.810 --> 00:09:48.280
You see, the neighboring land
had a sudden drought.

224
00:09:48.280 --> 00:09:49.530
You follow?

225
00:09:49.530 --> 00:09:54.240
Dance powder prematurely
grows clouds by artificial means

226
00:09:54.240 --> 00:09:59.410
before they are given time to become
rain clouds farther downwind,

227
00:09:59.410 --> 00:10:02.080
and forces young clouds to rain. So–

228
00:10:02.080 --> 00:10:03.040
Oh, I get it!

229
00:10:03.040 --> 00:10:07.840
It steals rain that would've normally
gone to a neighboring country!

230
00:10:08.210 --> 00:10:13.800
As a result, the two countries
went to war, and many lives were lost.

231
00:10:13.800 --> 00:10:17.050
The World Government put
a general ban on dance powder,

232
00:10:17.050 --> 00:10:19.140
prohibiting both production and usage.

233
00:10:19.140 --> 00:10:22.600
Powder that can bring both happiness
and sorrow when used...

234
00:10:22.600 --> 00:10:27.110
When that large shipment of
dance powder arrived at the port town,

235
00:10:27.110 --> 00:10:29.980
Alabasta was in the midst
of a weather phenomenon;

236
00:10:29.980 --> 00:10:33.070
the only place with rainfall
was the king's city.

237
00:10:34.070 --> 00:10:39.330
The rain stopped falling here because
the king is using dance powder!

238
00:10:39.330 --> 00:10:42.790
Alubarna's rain wasn't
a miracle after all!

239
00:10:42.790 --> 00:10:48.040
It's all that king's fault
everyone's parched and starving!

240
00:10:48.040 --> 00:10:51.340
Hold on, Vivi! That means
your dad is the bad guy here!

241
00:10:51.340 --> 00:10:53.720
You idiot! He was obviously framed!

242
00:10:53.720 --> 00:10:56.260
Vivi's father would
never do such a thing!

243
00:10:56.260 --> 00:11:00.140
Never! Never! Never!
Never! Never! Never!

244
00:11:01.430 --> 00:11:07.480
Of course, my father had nothing
to do with it... but during that same time...

245
00:11:08.360 --> 00:11:12.280
a massive amount of dance powder
was discovered inside the palace.

246
00:11:12.690 --> 00:11:15.740
He even had people working
inside the palace?

247
00:11:17.740 --> 00:11:20.530
What kind of road is this, Vivi?

248
00:11:20.530 --> 00:11:25.290
This was an irrigation canal that once
carried water from the Sandora River.

249
00:11:26.370 --> 00:11:29.250
But someone came through
and destroyed it.

250
00:11:29.960 --> 00:11:34.590
With its canal gone, the City of Green
could no longer secure water.

251
00:11:35.380 --> 00:11:40.600
People prayed and held out hope,
but the rain never came.

252
00:11:43.020 --> 00:11:48.060
Ever since the dance powder incident,
distrust in the king grows daily.

253
00:11:48.060 --> 00:11:50.900
All according to Crocodile's plan, huh?

254
00:11:51.360 --> 00:11:54.360
And then the fighting finally began.

255
00:11:55.440 --> 00:12:01.330
The people abandoned their cities,
weary of the constant skirmishes,

256
00:12:01.330 --> 00:12:04.290
and sought out oases
and other sources of water.

257
00:12:06.370 --> 00:12:07.210
And then...

258
00:12:09.750 --> 00:12:11.880
the City of Green withered away.

259
00:12:15.510 --> 00:12:16.630
Someone's collapsed!

260
00:12:16.630 --> 00:12:19.590
There are still people in this city?!

261
00:12:29.810 --> 00:12:31.110
What did my father...?

262
00:12:32.480 --> 00:12:35.480
What did the citizens
of this country ever do?

263
00:12:36.190 --> 00:12:38.320
This country is a harsh desert;

264
00:12:38.320 --> 00:12:40.610
the people struggle
against nature itself!

265
00:12:40.610 --> 00:12:44.160
Yet he has destroyed the lives
they fight so hard to maintain!

266
00:12:44.830 --> 00:12:48.660
What... What gives him
the right to do that?!

267
00:12:48.660 --> 00:12:49.670
What?!

268
00:12:51.250 --> 00:12:54.670
All the while, as one of
the Seven Warlords,

269
00:12:54.670 --> 00:12:56.590
he masquerades as the people's hero!

270
00:12:57.260 --> 00:13:02.430
No one realizes he's
deceiving the entire country!

271
00:13:02.430 --> 00:13:10.100
Crocodile! Crocodile! Crocodile!
Crocodile! Crocodile! Crocodile!

272
00:13:10.100 --> 00:13:11.310
I...

273
00:13:12.020 --> 00:13:14.020
can't let him get away with this!

274
00:13:22.990 --> 00:13:25.910
Really? Grow up already.

275
00:13:37.960 --> 00:13:38.760
Vivi!

276
00:13:39.130 --> 00:13:40.880
Let's get moving!

277
00:13:41.510 --> 00:13:43.050
I'm itching to do this now!

278
00:13:45.300 --> 00:13:47.430
Let's go to Yuba!

279
00:13:48.350 --> 00:13:50.520
The Rebel Army's there, right?

280
00:13:52.020 --> 00:13:55.810
Yes. I will persuade their leader
to end the rebellion.

281
00:13:55.810 --> 00:13:56.650
"Persuade"?

282
00:13:57.020 --> 00:14:00.570
All of Alabasta's calamities
are Crocodile's doing!

283
00:14:00.570 --> 00:14:01.900
Once he knows the truth,

284
00:14:01.900 --> 00:14:04.320
he will stop this pointless bloodshed!

285
00:14:04.320 --> 00:14:05.570
Got it.

286
00:14:19.670 --> 00:14:24.550
So hot... Water...

287
00:14:29.010 --> 00:14:32.480
Burning up... Sweat
won't even come out...

288
00:14:32.850 --> 00:14:36.860
Quit moaning so much, Luffy.
You'll only tire yourself out.

289
00:14:37.980 --> 00:14:39.820
Guess he's not listening.

290
00:14:42.650 --> 00:14:46.410
I can't go on. I can't take the heat.

291
00:14:46.410 --> 00:14:49.410
Cold weather, though? That's fine.

292
00:14:49.410 --> 00:14:53.790
It's all that fur. Just take off
your animal costume.

293
00:14:54.620 --> 00:14:56.920
You want me to do what now?

294
00:14:56.920 --> 00:14:59.550
You making fun of this reindeer?!

295
00:14:59.550 --> 00:15:01.510
Monster!

296
00:15:01.920 --> 00:15:05.130
Chopper! Turn big again
and the free ride is over!

297
00:15:05.130 --> 00:15:07.890
Who're you calling
a monster, monster-nose?!

298
00:15:07.890 --> 00:15:10.390
D-Don't be fooled!
I-I'll have you know this nose–

299
00:15:10.390 --> 00:15:12.350
Just change back already!

300
00:15:17.150 --> 00:15:20.520
You don't seem to be
having a hard time, Vivi.

301
00:15:20.520 --> 00:15:24.240
I was born and raised here,
so it doesn't bother me much.

302
00:15:24.240 --> 00:15:27.610
But... what's with all these hills?!

303
00:15:27.610 --> 00:15:31.200
I figured a desert would be more flat.

304
00:15:32.450 --> 00:15:35.250
This is a very old desert,

305
00:15:35.250 --> 00:15:38.500
so some sand dunes here
are over 300 meters high.

306
00:15:38.500 --> 00:15:40.630
Th-Three hundred meters?

307
00:15:40.630 --> 00:15:42.920
So that's why it's like...
climbing mountains...!

308
00:15:43.920 --> 00:15:46.930
It's too much... It's so hot...

309
00:15:47.300 --> 00:15:50.640
Just one drink, Luffy.
Just one mouthful.

310
00:15:52.890 --> 00:15:53.640
Too much!

311
00:15:53.640 --> 00:15:56.520
I'd like some too!
You just had thirteen mouthfuls!

312
00:15:56.520 --> 00:15:59.610
Not yet! You just had some! I'm next!

313
00:15:59.610 --> 00:16:03.190
Stop fighting! That's
how you waste energy!

314
00:16:03.650 --> 00:16:05.110
But she started it!

315
00:16:05.110 --> 00:16:06.450
It's your fault!

316
00:16:06.450 --> 00:16:08.200
Yeah! This is because of you!

317
00:16:08.200 --> 00:16:09.110
What?!

318
00:16:10.780 --> 00:16:13.740
Hey! Sanji! Let's have lunch!
A pirate lunch!

319
00:16:13.740 --> 00:16:17.160
Not yet. Not until Vivi says so.

320
00:16:17.160 --> 00:16:21.040
Come on, Vivi!
Let's eat! I'm outta strength!

321
00:16:21.040 --> 00:16:25.960
But we're only one tenth
of the way to Yuba, Luffy.

322
00:16:25.960 --> 00:16:29.130
How can you be so smart
if you haven't heard the old saying:

323
00:16:29.130 --> 00:16:31.220
"If you're hungry, eat!"?

324
00:16:31.220 --> 00:16:33.680
You liar! Quit making stuff up!

325
00:16:34.180 --> 00:16:35.310
All right.

326
00:16:35.310 --> 00:16:38.560
How about we stop
at the next rocky area?

327
00:16:38.560 --> 00:16:40.020
Cool! Looking for rocks!

328
00:16:40.020 --> 00:16:42.810
Everyone! We're gonna hurry
to the next rocky area!

329
00:16:42.810 --> 00:16:46.030
Whoever wins Rock Paper Scissors
carries everyone's stuff!

330
00:16:46.030 --> 00:16:47.360
Quit deciding things!

331
00:16:47.360 --> 00:16:49.030
Alright, here goes!

332
00:16:49.030 --> 00:16:50.070
Rock!

333
00:16:50.070 --> 00:16:51.070
Rock! Paper!

334
00:16:51.070 --> 00:16:51.780
Rock! Paper! Scissors!

335
00:16:51.780 --> 00:16:52.700
Wait, please!

336
00:16:52.700 --> 00:16:53.950
Hey! You went after!

337
00:16:53.950 --> 00:16:56.750
Woo-hoo! I win!

338
00:16:55.990 --> 00:16:56.750
Idiot.

339
00:17:00.080 --> 00:17:04.040
H-Heavy... So heavy... And hot...

340
00:17:04.040 --> 00:17:06.300
I won Rock Paper Scissors,
so why me?

341
00:17:06.300 --> 00:17:10.050
It's because you won.
Now shut up and haul.

342
00:17:10.050 --> 00:17:11.800
Don't drop it, now!

343
00:17:18.730 --> 00:17:21.190
Hey! Rocky outcropping,
dead ahead!

344
00:17:21.560 --> 00:17:22.560
Really?!

345
00:17:22.940 --> 00:17:26.070
Break time! Food!

346
00:17:26.070 --> 00:17:28.030
Whoa! He's fast!

347
00:17:31.950 --> 00:17:35.950
Finally! Shade! Feels so good!

348
00:17:54.720 --> 00:17:57.260
Bad news!

349
00:17:57.260 --> 00:17:59.350
And just like that, he's coming back?

350
00:17:59.350 --> 00:18:03.190
There's this group of birds
in real bad shape! Chopper!

351
00:18:03.940 --> 00:18:05.190
Right!

352
00:18:06.000 --> 00:18:09.110
Alright! Let's go, Chopper!

353
00:18:08.320 --> 00:18:09.110
Yeah!

354
00:18:09.650 --> 00:18:11.490
We gotta help these birds!

355
00:18:11.490 --> 00:18:12.360
Birds?!

356
00:18:12.360 --> 00:18:15.070
Wait, Luffy! These birds
sound like... Oh, no!

357
00:18:16.450 --> 00:18:17.330
Huh?

358
00:18:20.290 --> 00:18:21.960
They robbed us blind!

359
00:18:21.960 --> 00:18:23.790
We've been had...

360
00:18:24.580 --> 00:18:28.880
It's true, though! The birds here were
really about to kick the bucket!

361
00:18:29.450 --> 00:18:30.740
I'm sorry.

362
00:18:30.740 --> 00:18:32.800
I should have informed you sooner.

363
00:18:33.800 --> 00:18:38.260
Rogue herons, or desert bandits,
trick travelers and steal their supplies.

364
00:18:38.260 --> 00:18:40.720
What?!

365
00:18:41.730 --> 00:18:45.520
The birds play dead?
What a buncha liars!

366
00:18:45.520 --> 00:18:47.520
Yes, that's their nature.

367
00:18:47.520 --> 00:18:49.190
Then they tricked me!

368
00:18:49.190 --> 00:18:51.990
Luffy! Is that all you can
say for yourself?!

369
00:18:51.990 --> 00:18:54.490
We packed three days'
worth of provisions,

370
00:18:54.490 --> 00:18:56.660
and you let those birds
take everything!

371
00:18:56.660 --> 00:19:01.790
We're smack dab in the middle of a desert
without even a change of clothes!

372
00:19:01.790 --> 00:19:04.920
How do we cross a desert
when there's no food or water?!

373
00:19:04.920 --> 00:19:08.170
It's not my fault. They tricked me.

374
00:19:08.170 --> 00:19:10.590
How are you dumber than a bird?!

375
00:19:10.590 --> 00:19:11.550
Dumber than what?!

376
00:19:12.050 --> 00:19:13.590
Stop it, you two!

377
00:19:15.180 --> 00:19:16.470
It's no use.

378
00:19:16.970 --> 00:19:20.850
At times like this,
it's best to let them have it out.

379
00:19:22.100 --> 00:19:23.230
Fair point.

380
00:19:24.390 --> 00:19:27.850
Let's take a short break.
This heat is melting their brains.

381
00:19:29.110 --> 00:19:31.020
Food-wise, we'll manage.

382
00:19:31.530 --> 00:19:35.320
Being hungry hasn't killed us yet.
No use thinking about it.

383
00:19:35.320 --> 00:19:38.780
Yeah. Those thoughts
just get me thirstier.

384
00:19:52.170 --> 00:19:56.300
Give us our stuff back!

385
00:19:56.300 --> 00:19:58.680
Luffy! Don't chase them!

386
00:19:58.680 --> 00:20:00.010
That birdbrain.

387
00:20:00.010 --> 00:20:02.890
Hey! You'll lose your way back!

388
00:20:02.890 --> 00:20:05.600
Just come back, Luffy!

389
00:20:08.190 --> 00:20:11.570
Stop! You can't get away from me!

390
00:20:17.150 --> 00:20:18.860
Get back here!

391
00:20:23.200 --> 00:20:25.450
What's taking Luffy so long?!

392
00:20:26.080 --> 00:20:29.170
Yeah. Do you think he got lost?

393
00:20:29.170 --> 00:20:32.960
Luffy is dreadfully unaware
of the all the desert dangers.

394
00:20:35.760 --> 00:20:36.510
What's that?!

395
00:20:42.970 --> 00:20:44.850
What's this rumbling?!

396
00:20:52.150 --> 00:20:54.520
Another sandstorm?!

397
00:20:55.230 --> 00:20:57.360
No, wait! That's...

398
00:21:00.610 --> 00:21:01.450
Luffy!

399
00:21:01.820 --> 00:21:03.950
No... it's not possible!

400
00:21:06.790 --> 00:21:09.330
Why is he on a camel?!

401
00:21:11.580 --> 00:21:14.460
Not important! What's chasing him?!

402
00:21:14.460 --> 00:21:15.590
Hard to tell!

403
00:21:15.590 --> 00:21:18.800
It looks like something's
surging through the sand!

404
00:21:20.510 --> 00:21:25.390
It's huge!

405
00:21:23.220 --> 00:21:24.510
What?!

406
00:21:24.510 --> 00:21:25.390
What the...?!

407
00:21:25.720 --> 00:21:27.100
A Sandora dragon!

408
00:21:27.100 --> 00:21:28.600
A-A-A wh-what now?!

409
00:21:28.600 --> 00:21:34.110
The largest of the desert's reptiles,
they wait under the sand for their prey!

410
00:21:34.110 --> 00:21:38.650
They have sharp claws and teeth,
but they rarely need to use them!

411
00:21:38.650 --> 00:21:43.530
They are so big, they tend
to just swallow their prey whole!

412
00:21:44.030 --> 00:21:47.490
He really does have a gift
for attracting trouble.

413
00:21:47.490 --> 00:21:50.120
We can settle the camel thing later.

414
00:21:50.120 --> 00:21:54.040
What star was he born under
to become such a magnet for trouble?!

415
00:21:54.040 --> 00:21:56.290
Hey! Camel! Stop!

416
00:21:58.050 --> 00:21:59.800
Luffy! In over your head?!

417
00:21:59.800 --> 00:22:01.170
We'll lend a hand!

418
00:22:01.170 --> 00:22:02.930
Yeah! I brought some meat!

419
00:22:02.930 --> 00:22:04.300
Here goes, lizard!

420
00:22:04.300 --> 00:22:05.180
Gum-Gum...

421
00:22:05.180 --> 00:22:05.850
Dragon...

422
00:22:05.850 --> 00:22:06.760
Épaule...

423
00:22:06.760 --> 00:22:07.260
Whip!

424
00:22:07.260 --> 00:22:07.810
Twister!

425
00:22:07.810 --> 00:22:08.390
Shoot!

426
00:22:17.110 --> 00:22:18.860
Wh-Why take things so far?

427
00:22:18.860 --> 00:22:22.320
When they're fighting,
you almost pity the monsters.

428
00:22:30.160 --> 00:22:33.620
Check it out! These rocks
are natural frying pans!

429
00:22:34.670 --> 00:22:37.840
So, what's with the camel?

430
00:22:39.630 --> 00:22:40.380
Dunno.

431
00:22:40.380 --> 00:22:43.970
I saw a mystery plant trying to eat it
while I was chasing the birds.

432
00:22:43.970 --> 00:22:46.140
It doesn't seem to be a wild camel.

433
00:22:46.140 --> 00:22:49.060
No. It even has a saddle.

434
00:22:50.180 --> 00:22:54.140
Great, so we can ride it?!
What a lucky break!

435
00:22:54.140 --> 00:22:57.610
Yeah, that'll be a real help!
Looks like there's room for two!

436
00:22:57.980 --> 00:23:00.480
Camels do go hand-in-hand
with deserts!

437
00:23:00.480 --> 00:23:02.780
Then don't mind if I–

438
00:23:03.990 --> 00:23:04.990
What's your deal?!

439
00:23:05.490 --> 00:23:09.240
"I am a freedom-loving, hard-boiled,
compassionate camel!"

440
00:23:09.240 --> 00:23:12.250
"Thanks for helping me out back there."

441
00:23:12.250 --> 00:23:15.830
"I can give anyone a lift
as long as they're not a man."

442
00:23:19.420 --> 00:23:20.960
"I'm manly!"

443
00:23:21.760 --> 00:23:24.300
– Quit being stupid!
– Why, you...!

444
00:23:25.630 --> 00:23:29.640
You poor thing! My crewmates
weren't bred for manners.

445
00:23:29.640 --> 00:23:32.220
I think you're a good boy!
What should we call you?

446
00:23:32.220 --> 00:23:33.220
Idiot!

447
00:23:33.220 --> 00:23:33.890
Moron!

448
00:23:33.890 --> 00:23:34.680
Dumbass!

449
00:23:34.680 --> 00:23:36.350
Eyelashes it is, then!

450
00:23:36.350 --> 00:23:38.730
Um, that's the weirdest
one of the bunch.

451
00:23:39.310 --> 00:23:41.150
Okay! Get on, Vivi!

452
00:23:41.150 --> 00:23:44.110
No, I can still walk!

453
00:23:44.110 --> 00:23:45.030
Just get on.

454
00:23:45.030 --> 00:23:45.990
He's a pervy camel!

455
00:23:45.990 --> 00:23:46.780
Pervy camel!

456
00:23:46.780 --> 00:23:50.490
– Pervy camel! Pervy camel!
– Pervy camel! Pervy camel!

457
00:23:51.080 --> 00:23:53.750
We'll get there
a little faster now, right?

458
00:23:53.750 --> 00:23:57.790
The sooner we get to Yuba,
the sooner you talk to the Rebel Army!

459
00:23:58.330 --> 00:23:59.540
Giddyup, Eyelashes!

460
00:24:00.880 --> 00:24:02.210
Wait up!

461
00:24:02.670 --> 00:24:06.800
Hurry, guys! If we get separated,
you'll never leave the desert alive!

462
00:24:06.800 --> 00:24:07.800
You're the worst!

463
00:24:07.800 --> 00:24:09.800
But I still love you, Nami!

464
00:24:09.800 --> 00:24:11.050
After them! Hurry!

465
00:24:11.050 --> 00:24:12.010
Get on, Chopper!

466
00:24:12.010 --> 00:24:12.810
Yeah!

467
00:24:12.810 --> 00:24:14.850
Wait for us!
